  </div>
</section>

<!-- Animated Terminal Carousel -->
<TerminalCarousel />

<!-- Statistics Section -->
<section class="stats-section">
  <div class="stat-card">
    <span class="stat-number">$199B</span>
    <span class="stat-label">Agentic AI market by 2034</span>
    <a href="https://www.precedenceresearch.com/agentic-ai-market" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Precedence Research</a>
  </div>
  <div class="stat-card">
    <span class="stat-number">66%</span>
    <span class="stat-label">of developers frustrated with "almost right" AI code</span>
    <a href="https://survey.stackoverflow.co/2025/ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stack Overflow 2025</a>
  </div>
  <div class="stat-card">
    <span class="stat-number">39%</span>
    <span class="stat-label">of project failures due to requirements issues</span>
    <a href="https://zipdo.co/statistics/software-project-failure/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Zipdo Statistics</a>
  </div>
  <div class="stat-card">
    <span class="stat-number">48%</span>
    <span class="stat-label">of AI-generated code contains security vulnerabilities</span>
    <a href="https://www.qodo.ai/reports/state-of-ai-code-quality/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Qodo 2025</a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="feature-grid">
  <a href="/rtmx/guides/cli-reference" class="feature-card">
    <h3>One Command to See Everything</h3>
    <p>
      Know exactly where your project stands. <code>rtmx status</code> shows
      what's done, what's blocked, and what needs tests.
    </p>
  </a>

  <a href="/rtmx/guides/markers" class="feature-card">
    <h3>Proof, Not Promises</h3>
    <p>
      Every feature links to a test that proves it works.
      No more "I think it's covered."
    </p>
  </a>

  <a href="/rtmx/adapters/mcp" class="feature-card">
    <h3>AI That Knows Your Project</h3>
    <p>
      Claude, GPT, and other agents can query your requirements in real-time.
      They know what to build next.
    </p>
  </a>

  <a href="/rtmx/adapters" class="feature-card">
    <h3>Works With Your Tools</h3>
    <p>
      Sync to GitHub Issues, Jira, or keep everything local in version control.
      Your data, your choice.
    </p>
  </a>

  <a href="/rtmx/guides/dependencies" class="feature-card">
    <h3>See What's Blocking You</h3>
    <p>
      Visualize dependencies and find the critical path to done.
      Stop guessing what to work on next.
    </p>
  </a>

  <a href="/rtmx/guides/schema" class="feature-card">
    <h3>Catch Mistakes Before They Ship</h3>
    <p>
      Validate requirements against your team's standards automatically.
      Extensible for aerospace, medical, and defense.
    </p>
  </a>

  <a href="/rtmx/pricing" class="feature-card">
    <h3>Your Data Stays Yours</h3>
    <p>
      No cloud required. Open source and auditable.
      Git-native audit trail for compliance.
    </p>
  </a>

  <a href="/rtmx/reference/architecture" class="feature-card">
    <h3>Programmable Requirements</h3>
    <p>
      Full Python API. Query, filter, and automate from any script or notebook.
      Build custom workflows.
    </p>
  </a>

  <a href="/rtmx/pricing" class="feature-card coming-soon">
    <span class="badge">Coming Soon</span>
    <h3>Team Sync</h3>
    <p>
      CRDT-based collaboration with automatic conflict resolution.
      Multiple users, one source of truth.
    </p>
  </a>
</section>

<section class="comparison-section">
  <h2>AI writes code fast. But does it match your requirements?</h2>
  <p class="comparison-subtitle">Most tools track tasks. RTMX tracks whether the code actually does what you asked.</p>
  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table class="comparison-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Feature</th>
          <th>RTMX</th>
          <th>GitHub</th>
          <th>GitLab</th>
          <th>Jira</th>
          <th>Linear</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Test traceability</td>
          <td class="check">Built-in</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
          <td class="partial">Basic</td>
          <td class="cross">Plugin</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>pytest markers</td>
          <td class="check">Native</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>AI agent support</td>
          <td class="check">MCP</td>
          <td class="partial">Copilot</td>
          <td class="partial">Duo</td>
          <td class="cross">API only</td>
          <td class="cross">API only</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Requirements spec</td>
          <td class="check">CSV + Markdown</td>
          <td class="cross">Issues only</td>
          <td class="partial">Epics</td>
          <td class="check">Yes</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Git-native storage</td>
          <td class="check">Yes</td>
          <td class="cross">Database</td>
          <td class="cross">Database</td>
          <td class="cross">SaaS</td>
          <td class="cross">SaaS</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Self-hosted</td>
          <td class="check">Free</td>
          <td class="cross">Enterprise</td>
          <td class="check">Free</td>
          <td class="cross">$$$</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Open source</td>
          <td class="check">MIT</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
          <td class="partial">Core only</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>CLI-first workflow</td>
          <td class="check">Yes</td>
          <td class="partial">gh CLI</td>
          <td class="partial">glab CLI</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- "Why You Shouldn't Use RTMX" - Reverse Psychology Section -->
<section class="dont-use-section" id="dont-use">
  <h2><span class="strikethrough">DON'T</span> Use RTMX</h2>
  <p class="dont-use-intro">Seriously. It's not for everyone. Here's why you should probably stay away:</p>

  <div class="dont-use-grid">
    <div class="dont-use-card">
      <h3>You already have a spreadsheet.</h3>
      <p>
        Look, your <code>requirements.xlsx</code> file is working great. Sure, it's three tabs deep
        and nobody remembers which column means "done." But it's <em>free</em>. And you've been using it since 2019. Why change now?
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="dont-use-card">
      <h3>Your team doesn't use AI yet.</h3>
      <p>
        If you're not using Copilot, Claude Code, or Cursor, then RTMX won't help you. We're built for
        teams where AI writes half the code and humans need to keep it honest. If you're still typing every character yourself, godspeed.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="dont-use-card">
      <h3>You love Jira.</h3>
      <p>
        Really, you do. The 47 custom fields. The 12 workflow states. The satisfying click when you close
        a ticket that was open for 18 months. RTMX is just a CSV file and a CLI. Boring.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="dont-use-card">
      <h3>You don't want to pay $9.</h3>
      <p>
        The open-source version is free. Forever. Use that. If you don't need real-time sync across
        a team, you don't need to pay us anything. We mean it. Go ahead.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="dont-use-card">
      <h3>Budget approval sounds exhausting.</h3>
      <p>
        $9/user/month times 50 people is $5,400/year. That's a meeting. Maybe two meetings.
        And a Slack thread. And a Notion doc comparing alternatives. You know what? Just use the spreadsheet.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="dont-use-card">
      <h3>You ship fast and fix later.</h3>
      <p>
        Requirements traceability is for nerds who care about audits, compliance, and "knowing what the code does."
        If your philosophy is "we'll document it after Series B," RTMX will only slow you down.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="dont-use-card">
      <h3>You're worried we'll disappear.</h3>
      <p>
        Fair. We're small. We might get acqui-hired or pivot into oblivion. But here's the thing: your data is a CSV file.
        MIT license. You can <code>git log</code> your requirements forever. Zero lock-in. But yeah, maybe stick with the spreadsheet.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="dont-use-card">
      <h3>You don't get what it does.</h3>
      <p>
        "Requirements traceability matrix" sounds like something from a 1997 ISO handbook. And honestly? It kind of is.
        But if your AI is writing code that doesn't match your specs, and your tests don't prove you shipped what you promised... maybe that's fine?
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="still-reading">
    <p><strong>Still reading?</strong> Sounds like you might actually need RTMX.</p>
    <a href="/rtmx/quickstart" class="hero-button primary">Get Started</a>
  </div>
</section>

<footer class="site-footer">
  <p>
    Built by <a href="https://iotactical.co">ioTACTICAL Engineering</a> |
    <a href="mailto:engineering@iotactical.co">engineering@iotactical.co</a>
  </p>
</footer>

<style is:global>
  /* Hide Starlight's default hero/title on homepage */
  .hero,
  main > header,
  .content-panel > header,
  [aria-label="Main"] > header,
  .main-pane > h1:first-child,
  .sl-markdown-content > h1:first-child {
    display: none !important;
  }
</style>

<style>
  /* Hero Header - Title at very top */
  .hero-header {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 4rem 2rem 2rem;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0a0a0a 0%, #0f0f0f 100%);
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981 0%, #6ee7b7 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: #9ca3af;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    max-width: 850px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .hero-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .hero-button {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
  }

  .hero-button.primary {
    background: #10b981;
    color: #0a0a0a;
  }

  .hero-button.primary:hover {
    background: #6ee7b7;
  }

  .hero-button.secondary {
    background: transparent;
    color: #10b981;
    border: 2px solid #10b981;
  }

  .hero-button.secondary:hover {
    background: #10b981;
    color: #0a0a0a;
  }

  .github-button {
    background: #10b981;
    color: #0a0a0a;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
  }

  .github-button:hover {
    background: #6ee7b7;
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.4);
  }

  /* Hero Illustration - Full width */
  .hero-illustration-section {
    width: 100%;
    background: #0f0f0f;
    padding: 2rem 1rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .hero-illustration-container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .hero-illustration-container img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  /* Feature Grid */
  .feature-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 4rem 2rem;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    background: #0f0f0f;
  }

  .feature-card {
    background: #171717;
    border: 1px solid #262626;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-start;
  }

  .feature-card:hover {
    border-color: #10b981;
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .feature-card h3 {
    color: #f9fafb;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .feature-card p {
    color: #9ca3af;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .feature-card code {
    background: #262626;
    color: #e5e7eb;
    padding: 0.15em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    font-size: 0.85em;
  }

  .feature-card.coming-soon {
    position: relative;
    border-color: #f59e0b40;
    justify-content: flex-start;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .feature-card.coming-soon h3,
  .feature-card.coming-soon p {
    width: 100%;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .feature-card.coming-soon:hover {
    border-color: #f59e0b;
  }

  .feature-card .badge {
    position: absolute;
    top: -10px;
    right: 1rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f59e0b 0%, #d97706 100%);
    color: #0a0a0a;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  /* Statistics Section */
  .stats-section {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    background: #0a0a0a;
    border-top: 1px solid #262626;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #262626;
    align-items: stretch;
  }

  .stat-card {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: flex-start;
  }

  .stat-number {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981 0%, #6ee7b7 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
    line-height: 1;
    height: 3.5rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .stat-label {
    display: block;
    color: #9ca3af;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .stat-card a {
    display: inline-block;
    color: #6b7280;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .stat-card a:hover {
    color: #10b981;
  }

  /* Comparison Section */
  .comparison-section {
    padding: 4rem 2rem;
    background: #0a0a0a;
  }

  .comparison-section h2 {
    color: #f9fafb;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 1.75rem;
  }

  .comparison-subtitle {
    color: #9ca3af;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .table-wrapper {
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .comparison-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    background: #171717;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    overflow: hidden;
    table-layout: fixed;
  }

  .comparison-table th,
  .comparison-table td {
    padding: 1rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #262626;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }

  .comparison-table th:first-child,
  .comparison-table td:first-child {
    text-align: left;
    width: 25%;
  }

  .comparison-table th:not(:first-child),
  .comparison-table td:not(:first-child) {
    width: 15%;
  }

  .comparison-table th {
    background: #0f0f0f;
    color: #f9fafb;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .comparison-table td {
    color: #d1d5db;
  }

  .comparison-table .check {
    color: #22c55e;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .comparison-table .cross {
    color: #6b7280;
  }

  .comparison-table .partial {
    color: #f59e0b;
  }

  .comparison-table .coming-soon {
    color: #f59e0b;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Footer */
  .site-footer {
    padding: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-top: 1px solid #262626;
    background: #0a0a0a;
  }

  .site-footer p {
    color: #6b7280;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .site-footer a {
    color: #10b981;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .site-footer a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* "DON'T Use RTMX" Section */
  .dont-use-section {
    background: #070707;
    padding: 4rem 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #262626;
  }

  .dont-use-section h2 {
    color: #f9fafb;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .dont-use-section h2 .strikethrough {
    text-decoration: line-through;
    text-decoration-color: #ef4444;
    text-decoration-thickness: 3px;
  }

  .dont-use-intro {
    color: #9ca3af;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .dont-use-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    grid-auto-rows: 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .dont-use-card {
    background: #0d0d0d;
    border: 1px solid #1f1f1f;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-start;
    height: 100%;
  }

  .dont-use-card h3 {
    color: #e5e7eb;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
  }

  .dont-use-card p {
    color: #6b7280;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .dont-use-card code {
    background: #1a1a1a;
    color: #9ca3af;
    padding: 0.15em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    font-size: 0.85em;
  }

  .dont-use-card em {
    color: #9ca3af;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .still-reading {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #1f1f1f;
  }

  .still-reading p {
    color: #d1d5db;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .still-reading .hero-button.primary {
    background: #10b981;
    color: #0a0a0a;
    padding: 0.875rem 2rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .still-reading .hero-button.primary:hover {
    background: #6ee7b7;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .feature-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }

    .stats-section {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-header {
      padding: 2rem 1rem;
    }

    .hero-title {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }

    .hero-subtitle {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .hero-buttons {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .stats-section {
